Fill a large pan with salted water and bring to the boil. Add the potatoes and cook until soft. Drain and mash.In a bowl, combine the crab meat, mashed potatoes, cheese, egg, spring onion, chives and lemon zest.  Season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Add the sweet chilli sauce and stir through.Dust your hands and a work surface with flour. Use your hands to pat the mixture into little circular cakes.Fry the cakes in the butter until golden-brown on each side. This should take about 2-3 minutes on each sideServe immediately with a side salad.